title: Naive Player Playthrough
story: guess-the-verb
description: A first-time IF player stumbles through the game using natural language

---

## Front Porch — fumbling around

# A naive player looks around first
> look
[OK: contains "Front Porch"]
[OK: contains "doormat"]
[OK: contains "doorbell"]

# They try to examine things they see mentioned
> examine doormat
[OK: contains "doormat"]

> examine doorbell
[OK: contains "brass"]

# A naive player tries to "ring" the doorbell — natural English
> ring doorbell
[OK: contains "doorbell"]

# They try to take the mat — should reveal the key (not blank)
> take mat
[OK: contains "iron key"]

# They try lifting the mat again — key already revealed
> lift mat
[OK: contains "already"]

# Maybe they try "look under"
> look under mat
[OK: contains "key"]

# They see the key and take it
> take key
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# A naive player might try "use key on door"
> unlock door with key
[OK: contains "unlock"]

> open door
[OK: contains "open"]

> east
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

## Hallway — searching and climbing

# They see the overcoat mentioned and try natural verbs
> examine overcoat
[OK: contains "overcoat"]

# "check pockets" is a very natural thing to try
> search pockets
[OK: contains "matches"]

# They see a staircase mentioned, try to climb it
> climb stairs
[OK: contains_any "up" "Up" "UP" "stairs" "Attic"]

# The game hints to go UP, so the naive player tries that
> up
[OK: contains "Attic"]

## Study — fire and painting puzzles

# They went up, now back down to continue exploring
> down
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

> east
[OK: contains "Study"]

# They see a desk and try to open it
> open desk
[OK: contains "open"]

# Take what's inside
> take winding key
[OK: contains_any "Taken" "winding"]

# They see a painting and try to look behind it
> look behind painting
[OK: contains_any "painting" "safe" "wall"]

# They notice the fireplace and try to light it
> light fireplace
[OK: contains_any "fire" "match" "glow" "warmth" "7" "hearthstone"]

# They notice the numbers
> examine hearthstone
[OK: contains "7"]

# They know the combo now, try to open the safe
> dial 7 3 9
[OK: contains_any "Click" "click" "open" "safe"]

# Take what's inside
> take spring
[OK: contains_any "Taken" "spring" "clock"]

## Garden — digging

> west
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

> south
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

> south
[OK: contains "Garden"]

# They see the trowel
> take trowel
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# A naive player might just type "dig" with no target
> dig
[OK: contains_any "dig" "flower" "earth" "soft"]

# Or they might try "dig flower bed"
> dig flower bed
[OK: contains_any "mechanism" "brass" "music"]

> take mechanism
[OK: contains "Taken"]

## Attic — assembly and victory

> north
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

> north
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

> up
[OK: contains "Attic"]

# They see the music box and try to fix it
> examine music box
[OK: contains "music box"]

> take music box
[OK: contains "music box"]

> put mechanism in music box
[OK: contains "mechanism"]

> put spring in music box
[OK: contains "spring"]

# Now wind it
> wind music box
[OK: contains_any "melody" "wind" "release" "trunk"]

# The trunk opened! A naive player opens it
> open trunk
[OK: contains_any "open" "trunk" "locket"]

> take locket
[OK: contains "locket"]
